         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>8, 255</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>234</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... it is not surprising that old, wretched or poor people leave the house and go to Buddha ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>240</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">very amazing and very surprising [is] yet the monkhood of Nanda ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he went in front of Nanda approaching in a revering manner ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... but this lay-woman was [like] a Kālinga textile to touch ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... retain the body ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">und er konnte sich nicht zurückhalten</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">and he could not contain himself</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>310</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">le Buddha-seigneur, le maître, prit connaissance de l'affaire.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>14</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>194</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>263</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... thereupon, Viśākhā touched her own head, and immediately she knew ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Darauf strich sich Viśākhā nur über ihren Kopf [und] sogleich wusste sie: ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Thereupon Viśākhā merely stroked her head [and] immediately she knew: ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>285</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
